          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>HHS Cybersecurity Modernization Act</strong></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to designate an officer within HHS as having the primary responsibility of information security, including cybersecurity, for HHS programs; HHS may transfer the functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the previous Chief Information Security Officer within HHS to the newly designated officer.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-10-31T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
